 Jose Mourinho has been sacked by Tottenham Hotspur just six days before the Carabao Cup final against Manchester City at Wembley Stadium. The 58-year-old Portuguese coach was appointed as Tottenham manager in November 2019, a day after the sacking of Mauricio Pochettino. Mourinho guided the North London team to sixth place in the table by the end of the campaign, but his style of football often didn’t win him much acclaim from fans. Tottenham have struggled at time in the Premier League this season and embarrassingly exited the Europa League at the last-16 stage after a 3-2 aggregate defeat to Dinamo Zagreb. According to Tottenham Hotspurs, official Twitter to announce that Mourinho and his coaching staff Joao Sacramento, Nuno Santos, Carlos Lalin and Giovanni Cerra. The Club can today announce that Jose Mourinho and his coaching staff Joao Sacramento, Nuno Santos, Carlos Lalin and Giovanni Cerra have been relieved of their duties.#THFC ⚪️ #COYS — Tottenham Hotspur (@SpursOfficial) April 19, 2021 However, the club former player Mason has been appointed to replace Mourinho as the new Tottenham Hotspurs coach until the end of the season along with Chris Powell in the dugout ahead of the Carabao Cup final over the weekend. Mourinho’s last game in charge at Tottenham Hotspurs came in the 2-2 draw against Everton on Friday at Goodison Park with a brace from Harry Kane and Gylfi Sigurdsson. Post Views: 
